ll-known name and use that when"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"processing the received signal.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If one of ","type":"text"},{"code":"matchArg0Namespace","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"matchArg0Path"},{"text":" are given, ","type":"text"},{"code":"arg0","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interpreted as part of a namespace or path.  The first argument"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of a signal is matched against that part as specified by D-Bus."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If "},{"code":"userDataFreeFunc","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is non-","type":"text"},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", it will be called (in the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"thread-default main context of the thread you are calling this"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"method from) at some point after "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"userData"},{"text":" is no longer","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"needed. (It is not guaranteed to be called synchronously when the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"signal is unsubscribed from, and may be called after "},{"code":"connection","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"has been destroyed.)","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As "},{"code":"callback","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is potentially invoked in a different thread from where it’s","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"emitted, it’s possible for this to happen after","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_dbus_connection_signal_unsubscribe()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" has been called in another thread.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Due to this, "},{"code":"userData","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" should have a strong reference which is freed with"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"userDataFreeFunc","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", rather than pointing to data whose lifecycle is tied"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to the signal subscription. For example, if a [Object](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/object is used to store the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"subscription ID from "},{"code":"g_dbus_connection_signal_subscribe()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", a strong reference","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to that [Object](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/object must be passed to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"userData"},{"type":"text","text":", and "},{"code":"g_object_unref()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" passed to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"userDataFreeFunc"},{"text":". You are responsible for breaking the resulting","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reference count cycle by explicitly unsubscribing from the signal when"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"dropping the last external reference to the [Object](\/\/documentation\/gobject\/object. Alternatively, a weak"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reference may be used."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It is guaranteed that if you unsubscribe from a signal using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_dbus_connection_signal_unsubscribe()"},{"text":" from the same thread which made the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"corresponding ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_dbus_connection_signal_subscribe()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" call, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"callback"},{"type":"text","text":" will not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"be invoked after "},{"code":"g_dbus_connection_signal_unsubscribe()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" returns."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The returned subscription identifier is an opaque value which is guaranteed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to never be zero.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This function can never fail."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Subscribes to signals on ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"connection"},{"text":" and invokes ","type":"text"},{"code":"callback","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" whenever","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"the signal is received. Note that ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"callback"},{"type":"text","text":" will be invoked in the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"thread-default main context (see [method"},{"code":"GLib.MainContext.push_thread_default","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"])","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"of the thread you are calling this method from."}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/gio\/dbusconnection\/signalsubscribe(sender:interfacename:member:objectpath:arg0:flags:callback:userdata:userdatafreefunc:)"]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GIO\/documentation\/GIO\/DBusConnection\/signalSubscribe(sender:interfaceName:member:objectPath:arg0:flags:callback:userData:userDataFreeFunc:)","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"signalSubscribe","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"sender"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"UnsafePointer","kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:SP"},{"text":"<","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifie